sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.country_name
FROM countries c
JOIN population_data pd ON c.country_id = pd.country_id
WHERE pd.life_expectancy > 75 AND pd.life_expectancy < (
  SELECT AVG(life_expectancy) FROM population_data
);

external_knowledge:
- "nurturing the seeds of life" metaphorically refers to the care and conditions that affect life expectancy for very young children (0-4 years).;
- "promise higher than the global average" means the average life expectancy for this age group exceeds the worldwide average.;
- "early stages" refers to the age range of 0 to 4 years.

